  "prompt": "How much money can I deposit in my account?",
  "response": "The amount of money you can deposit into your account depends on several factors, including:\n\n1. **Bank or Financial Institution Policies**: Some banks may have daily or monthly deposit limits, especially for online or mobile deposits.\n\n2. **Account Type**: Different types of accounts (e.g., savings, checking) may have different limits.\n\n3. **Method of Deposit**: If you're depositing cash at an ATM, there might be a limit to how much can be processed in a single transaction. For checks, some banks impose limits on the mobile deposit amounts.\n\n4. **Regulatory Limits**: While there generally aren't federal restrictions on deposit amounts in the U.S., very large deposits might require additional verification or reporting due to anti-money laundering regulations.\n\n5. **Banking Services**: If using certain services like a prepaid card, there might be more stringent deposit limits compared to traditional banking.\n\nTo determine the specific amount you can deposit in your account, it's best to check directly with your bank's policies either by accessing their customer service, visiting their website, or checking your account agreement.",
